3:30 PM SENTENCING HEARING:  
ADA Matthew R. Leusink appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defendant Raul  Valadez Rayas in court, in custody with Attorney David Danz.  
The defendant has previously plead to Ct 1 of this file - OWI 5th.  
The parties have a joint agreement as to sentence and the defendant would like to proceed to sentencing today.  Mr. Valadez Rayas has another pending case, 2016CF000279, and is represented by Attorney Steve Compton on that matter.  Attorney Compton could not be here today due to medical issues.  File 2016CF000279 is scheduled for a Jury Trial on December 12 and 13 at 8:30 am and remains on for trial at this time.   Court has colloquy with Mr. Valadez Rayas.  He does wish to proceed to sentencing today.  Court imposes the agreed upon sentence of the parties:  

SENTENCE:  
Total length of sentence:  5 yrs prison;  
2 yrs IC followed by 3 yrs ES;  
142 days of sentence credit;  
36 months revocation of D.L. and I.I.D.;  
A & R;  
Eligible for CIP and SAP;  

Conditions of Extended Supervision:  
1)  Pay $1200 fine plus court costs and DOC supervision fees.  
2)  AODA assessment and follow through with any recommended treatment.  
3)  Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge.  
4)  Attend a Victim Impact Panel.
